        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook and blend",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{butternut-squash}}, {{onion}}, {{garlic}}, {{ginger-root}}, {{smoked-paprika}}, {{cumin-ground}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, {{black-pepper}}, and {{vegetable-oil}} to the slow cooker. Pour over the {{stock-vegetable}} and stir. Cook on low for 6 hours, until the squash is completely soft. Blend until smooth using a stick blender directly in the pot. If the soup is too thick, add more stock or water and blend again. Taste and adjust seasoning. Swirl in {{double-cream}} to finish if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Add hot stock or water and blend again. Adjust until the consistency pours easily from a ladle",
              "cause": "Squash released more liquid than expected and then reduced over 6 hours",
              "symptom": "Soup too thick after blending"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Season generously at the end, blended soups absorb salt differently. A squeeze of lemon juice also brightens a flat soup",
              "cause": "Insufficient seasoning or weak stock",
              "symptom": "Soup tastes bland despite the squash"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Start with 15 g rather than 20 g next time. A large pinch of sugar also balances excessive ginger heat",
              "cause": "Fresh ginger is strong when concentrated over 6 hours",
              "symptom": "Ginger flavour overpowering"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Butternut squash soup is the most reliable slow-cooker soup. The squash is forgiving, sweet, and produces a naturally smooth result when blended. It works as a weekday lunch or a dinner party starter. Serve with crusty bread and a swirl of cream or a scatter of toasted pumpkin seeds.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
